==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: pectic
<hw>pec"tic</hw> <pr>(p⟦ecr⟧k"t⟦icr⟧k)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>phkto`s</grk> curdled.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>Of or
pertaining to pectin; specifically, designating an acid obtained from
ordinary vegetable jelly (pectin) as an amorphous substance, tough and
horny when dry, but gelatinous when moist.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

